<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fance Wins European Championship with Golden Goal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROTTERDAM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- France rallied to beat Italy 2-1
with Substitute David Trezeguet's golden goal in the 103rd minute
to win the Euro 2000 final on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
France became the first reigning world champions to win the
European title.
</P>
<P>
Marco Delvecchio had given Italy the lead in the 56th minute
when he volleyed home a Gianluca Pessotto cross from close range.
</P>
<P>
Italy seemed to be heading for certain victory but French
substitute Sylvain Wiltord broke through down the left in the last
minute of four minutes of stoppage time and stabbed home the
equaliser.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
