<HEADLINE> France Equalizes against Italy after 90 Minutes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROTTERDAM, July 2 (Xinhua) -- France equalized against Italy in
the last minute to send the Euro 2000 final into extra time with a
1-1 tie after 90 minutes on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Sylvain Wiltord broke free on the left in the last
minute of four minutes of stoppage time to equalize.
</P>
<P>
Italy led the world champion France 1-0 with a goal from Marco
Delvecchio in the 56th minute.  
</P>
</TEXT>
