<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Defeats Qingdao 2-1 in Chinese First Division League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, Yunnan Province, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Hongta
overcame a one-goal deficit at half-time to beat visiting Qingdao
Hainiu 2-1 in China's first division soccer league here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
After trailing 1-0 at break, Yunnan defender Liu Yue blasted a
powerful shot in the 70th minute. The Qingdao goalie tried to save
but could only see the ball bounced off his hands to land in the
net.
</P>
<P>
Ten minutes later, Yunnan midfielder Chang Hui was fouled while
dribbling in the area and was awarded a penalty kick, which was
converted to seal Yunnan's victory.
</P>
<P>
In Chengdu, Sichuan Province, a header from Yao Xia gave
Sichuan Quanxin a 1-0 victory over visiting Jilin Aodong.
</P>
<P>
In the 35th minute, Yao, who is only 1.68-meter tall, soared
unexpectedly above the higher players to head in the ball.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, Beijing Guo'an squandered a 2-0 half-time lead
before being forced to a 3-3 tie by visiting Shanghai Shenhua.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao of Beijing and Shanghai's Qi Hong scored a double each,
with Wang netting twice in the first half and Qi in the second.
</P>
<P>
It was the second consecutive game that Wang scored a double.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Shandong Luneng beat Shenzhen Ping'an 3-1 while
Xiamen Xiaxin tied with Shenyang Haishi 1-1.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Fushun lost to Dalian Shide 2-1 and Chongqing Longxin
tied with visitors Tianjin Taida 1-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
