<HEADLINE> Xinhua Middle East News Summary at 2100 GMT, Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel is considering transferring about 1,000
former Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army (SLA) militiamen and their
family members to other countries, a Interior Ministry official
disclosed Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of such ex-SLA militiamen wanting to move abroad
will be flown to Germany next week if all bureaucratic procedures
are smooth as expected, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Israel is also conducting intensive talks with other countries,
mostly in North and South America, to persuade them to absorb some
SLA refugees.
</P>
<P>
Some 6,000 SLA militiamen and their family members have been
taking shelter in Israel since May after their army collapsed under
pressure of Lebanese resistance guerrillas, and Israel withdrew
from the so-called security zone in south Lebanon later. (Israel-
SLA Refugees)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- The Palestinian Liberation Organization's Central
Committee convenes here Sunday to discuss preparations for a
Palestinian state later this year.
</P>
<P>
One hundred and twenty-nine members of the committee from
various PLO factions attended the two-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat has said that he is determined
to declare an independent Palestinian state with Jerusalem as its
capital this year - with or without a peace treaty with Israel.
(PLO-Statehood)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- No date has been set for a three-way summit in
Washington to discuss the Middle East peace process, Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Briefing his cabinet about the ongoing Israeli-Palestinian
final-status talks and the proposed three-way summit between
himself, Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and U.S. President Bill
Clinton, Barak said Clinton has not made up his mind to call the
summit in the near future.
</P>
<P>
"Only President Clinton has the right to decide on when to hold
this summit, but the president decided to postpone to make such a
decision and therefore there will be no three-way summit for the
near future," Barak said. (Israel-Barak-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- An agreement has been concluded between Kuwait
and Saudi Arabia for the demarcation of sea borders during an
ongoing visit paid by Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz to
Kuwait. The Kuwaiti News Agency reported Saudi Foreign
Minister Saud Al-Faisal signed for Saudi Arabia, while Kuwaiti
First Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah al-
Ahmad al-Jaber al-Sabah signed for Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The sea border has been a question of contention between both
countries for 80 years. The two parties agreed to sharing oil
resources in the disputed area. (Kuwait-Saudi Arabia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel and India have agreed to establish a
diplomatic and security dialogue to further boost their bilateral
ties established eight years ago.
</P>
<P>
During the talks between visiting Indian Foreign Minister
Jaswant Singh and Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak and Foreign
Minister David Levy on Sunday, the leaders of both countries
discussed ways to cement ties in a spectrum of fields including
trade, weaponry as well as science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Levy also called on his Indian counterpart to join in the
efforts of fighting for the release of the 10 Jews convicted and
sentenced to prison terms by an Iranian court over espionage
charges.
 (Israel-India-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Visiting Indian Foreign Minister Jaswant Singh said here
Sunday that Jerusalem is part of the Israel-occupied territories,
and that India supports the Palestinians in their struggle to
establish an independent state.
</P>
<P>
Singh made the remarks during his talks with Faisal al-Husseini,
a member of the Palestinian Liberation Organization (PLO) executive
committee who is in charge of the dossier of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Al-Husseini briefed Singh on the situation of Jerusalem under
the Israeli occupation, and noted that the peace process between
Israel and the Palestinians urges the Israeli full withdrawal from
the occupied Palestinian territories including Jerusalem.
(Palestine-India-Jerusalem) 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
