<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia to Lift Oil Production by 500,000 bpd "Very Soon" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia will raise its oil
production by 500,000 barrels per day (bpd) "very soon" in an
effort to bring down the soaring oil prices in world market, Saudi
Minister of Petroleum and Mineral Resources Ali Bin al-N'aimi said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Al-N'aimi was quoted by the official SPA news agency as saying
that Saudi Arabia has acted and is acting to bring the prices down
from the current level of around 30 U.S. dollars per barrel to the
target level of 25 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
If the oil prices remain high, Saudi Arabia, along with other
oil producers, will increase production by 500,000 barrels a day
within the next few days.
</P>
<P>
The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)
announced at a meeting in Vienna last month that it would add 708,
000 barrels to the market from July 1 in an effort to curb high
prices. Despite the 708,000-barrel increase in production, oil
prices have remained above 30 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, the world's largest oil producer and exporter, had
reportedly been seeking to persuade other producers to raise
exports above the agreed-upon hike. 
</P>
</TEXT>
