<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Higher In Shortened Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks rose in a
shortened session Monday ahead of the U.S. Independence Day
holiday amid more signs of the slowing economy.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 112.78 at 10,560.67
and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 25.82 at 3,
991.93.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 14.72 at 1,469.32.
</P>
<P>
The market rallied after the National Association of Purchasing
Management reported that  its production index fell to 51.8
percent in June from 53.2 percent in May, considerable lower than
53 percent in expectation.
</P>
<P>
The latest report showed more signs of the slowdown in the U.S.
economy after the Federal Reserve raised interest rates six times
in the past year in an effort to cool off the economy and keep
inflation at bay. Investors, therefore, eased their worries about
more hike in rates that was expected possibly at the Federal
Reserve's August 22 meeting.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 7.26 at 650.19 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 7.51 at 943.40. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 6.81 at 524.04.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 2-to-1 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange with 1,991 up, 814 down and 431
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined 446.77 million shares in a shortened
session from 1.4 billion in the previous one.
</P>
<P>
The market was closed at 1 p.m.for the Independence Day holiday.
</P>
</TEXT>
