<HEADLINE> France to Reinforce Anti-Criminal Cooperation Within EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- France will reinforce cooperation
among European Union (EU) countries in the fight against trans-
frontier criminal activities, said French Interior Minister Jean-
Pierre Chevenement Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chevenement recalled that the EU summit held recently in Feira,
Portugal, has called for intensifying the cooperation between
European states.
</P>
<P>
He said that France, which took over the EU rotating presidency
from Portugal on July 1, will spare no effort in implementing the
EU decision.
</P>
<P>
France has set up a Central Section of Operational Cooperation
of Police in Nanterre near Paris to coordinate the French police
force working for the Interpol, Europol and the Schengen
borderless space's transnational police force.
</P>
<P>
The center is particularly in charge of the fight against
international organized crimes and modernizing the tools for
international cooperation in this field.
</P>
<P>
France will organize exchange of experiences among EU countries
in the operation against drug trafficking and will increase the
power of the Europol in fighting money laundering activities, said
Chevenement.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation in the fields of developing date of digital
fingerprints and genetic digitals as well as methods in fighting
high-tech and electronic crimes will also be launched, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
