<HEADLINE> Business Failures In Britain Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Business failures in Britain have
fallen to their lowest level since 1996, according to a report
released Monday by consultants Dun &AMP; Bradstreet.
</P>
<P>
It said 20,264 businesses collapsed during the first six months
of this year, compared with 21,287 for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
During the last three months, the number of business failures
totaled 9,554 -- the first time for more than a year that the
quarterly tally has dipped below 10,000.
</P>
<P>
Southern England led the boom, with business failures across
the region at the lowest level since 1990. Failures fell 10
percent to 3,992, as the region's economy boomed.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, business failures dropped most sharply
in London and there were decrease in most regions. But
manufacturing is still struggling, and there were rises in company
bankruptcies and liquidations in north-east and north-west England.
</P>
<P>
The report also showed that the failure rate dropping slightly
faster for larger businesses than smaller firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
