<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Rubber Export Up in 1st Part of 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam exported 105,000 tons of
rubber latex, earning 65 million U.S. dollars in the first six
months of this year, representing a year-on-year increase of 7.1
percent and 11.3 percent, respectively, Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Before 1990, VNA said, Vietnam exported 60 percent of its
rubber latex to the former Soviet Union, 20 percent to Singapore,
and 10 percent to Eastern Europe. But sales to those markets have
gradually dropped in recent years. At present, China is the main
customer of Vietnam's rubber. In the first six months of this year,
China absorbed 30 percent of Vietnam's rubber exports.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam have also expanded the export of rubber to other
outlets including Poland, Spain, Hong Kong, Sweden, Italy and the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam now has about 380,000 hectares of rubber. Its rubber
industry is disposing of low-quality rubber plantations and
introducing new rubber strains into cultivation to raise the
quality of rubber latex and boost domestic sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
