<HEADLINE> Brazil Withdraws 2006 World Cup Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazil have withdrawn their
candidature to host the 2006 World Cup and will instead be
supporting South Africa's bid, Brazilian Football Confederation (
CBF) president Ricardo Teixeira confirmed on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The move follows reports that football's world governing body
FIFA were favouring South Africa's bid, while the European body
UEFA were backing Germany.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's 24-man executive board meets on Thursday in Zurich to
decide which of the remaining four bidding countries -- England,
Germany, South Africa and Morocco -- will win the biggest prize in
sports. 
</P>
