<HEADLINE> China's Armed Forces Vow to Improve Ideological and Political Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The country's armed forces and
armed police have vowed to improve their ideological and political
work in line with the important speech made by Jiang Zemin, the
country's president and chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
</P>
<P>
In his speech to a Communist Party of China (CPC) conference on
ideological and political work last week, Jiang, also general
secretary of the CPC Central Committee, called for the party to
put more emphasis on socialist ideological and political education
to ensure that the country's modernization drive is a success.
</P>
<P>
Officers and men of the armed forces noted that Jiang's speech
represents a programmatic document for the party to make a
breakthrough in its ideological and political work in the new
century.
</P>
<P>
As a people's army under the CPC's absolute leadership, the
armed forces view effective ideological and political work as its
cherished tradition, which has enabled it to score one victory
after another, they said.
</P>
<P>
In their study of Jiang's speech, the officers and men also
discussed ways and means to further strengthen the ideological and
political work in the armed forces. 
</P>
