<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Council Stresses Industrial Safety (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All these accidents have shown that some local governments lack
a sense of responsibility. The meeting demanded that officials at
all levels put production safety at the top of their working
agendas.
</P>
<P>
The meeting urged the Guangdong provincial committee of the
Communist Party of China and the provincial government to spare no
efforts to complete the rescue and restoration work in aftermath
of the blast, to ensure social stability.
</P>
<P>
The meeting asked local governments to extend production safety
supervision work, with emphasis placed on the implementation of
the production safety regulations issued by the central government
and on the prevention of accidents. Local governments should to
submit reports to the central authorities on progress in this work
before the end of July.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also called for the perfection and implementation
of a production safety responsibility system which will ensure
severe punishment for people responsible for such accidents.
</P>
<P>
It was decided at the meeting that a State Council working
group be established, composed of officials of the State Economic
and Trade Commission, the Ministry of Public Security, the
Ministry of Supervision and the All-China Federation of Trade
Unions. The group will be responsible for the supervision of the
recent serious accidents and will report to the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The State Council working group will go to Guangdong, Hubei,
Sichuan and Chongqing to carry out an examination of the
production safety work in these areas and supervise how they
handle the above accidents. 
</P>
