<HEADLINE> Compensation Paid for Plane Crash Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Compensation has been paid to the
families of the victims of the June 22 plane crash near this
capital of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Sums of 200,000 yuan (about 24,096 U.S. dollars) have been paid
to the families of each of the 20 passengers who had taken out
life insurance policies; the families of the other victims have
been paid 121,100 yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two passengers and crew members were killed when a
Chinese-made Yun-7 passenger aircraft of Wuhan Airlines crashed
shortly before landing.
</P>
<P>
Seven people on the ground were also killed in the crash.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the crash is still under investigation. 
