<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Council Stresses Industrial Safety (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's State Council has ordered
local governments and departments concerned to take immediate
measures to ensure industrial safety, in the wake of the fireworks
factory explosion in south China's Guangdong Province last week.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, at 8:05 am last Friday in Jiangmen City, claimed
32 lives, and injured 17 people, with 39 other still missing.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin has expressed deep concern over
the accident. Other senior leaders, including Zhu Rongji, Hu
Jintao and Li Lanqing, have asked the Guangdong provincial
government to make arrangements for safety and rescue work in
enterprises throughout the province. The State Council called an
emergency meeting on the subject on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is pointed out that the central authorities have always paid
close attention to production safety, and laws and regulations
have been worked out for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
But a series of severe accidents have occurred, which include
the June 22 air crash in central China's Hubei Province, the June
22 Yangtze River shipwreck in southwest China's Sichuan Province,
and an explosion at the Dianjiang fireworks factory in Chongqing
Municipality.
</P>
</TEXT>
