<HEADLINE> Leading Artist Guan Shanyue Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Guan Shanyue, a celebrated
contemporary Chinese painting master and educator, died of illness
here at 17:08 today. He was 89.
</P>
<P>
Guan was described as an outstanding member of the Chinese
Communist Party, a people's artist and a master of art.
</P>
<P>
He was a deputy to the National People's Congress. He also
served as vice-chairman of the Chinese Artists' Association and
chairman of the Guangdong Provincial Artists' Association.
</P>
<P>
During Guan's illness, Chairman Li Ruihuan of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference made a phone call to him to express his sympathy.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials from Guan's native province of Guangdong and
noted figures from the art circles at home and abroad visited Guan
during his hospitalization. 
</P>
