<HEADLINE> One Million Students Bound for Rural Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Starting from today, over one
million students will go to rural areas for social practice work
this summer, according to the Central Committee of the Communist
Youth League of China.
</P>
<P>
More college students and professional school students have
participated in these activities this year than last year. In east
China's Jiangsu province alone, more than 300,000 students have
volunteered.
</P>
<P>
In addition, about 1,800 doctorate students will join the
activity, 60 percent of whom will go to the western regions of the
country to help improve the levels of science, culture and health
there.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government encourages young students to spend weeks
or months each summer living and working in impoverished villages,
learning the actual situation there and making contributions to
local development with their knowledge and talents. Since 1996,
tens of millions of students have taken part in these activities.
</P>
