<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Official Disciplined for Dereliction of Duty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A leading official in Benxi City,
in northeast China's Liaoning Province, has been disciplined for
dereliction of duty which caused heavy economic losses to the
state.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhida, former chairman of the Benxi City Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and former
general manager of the Benxi Iron and Steel Company, has been
deprived of all his posts as a result, central government
officials said here today.
</P>
<P>
Investigations revealed that in his post as the company's
general manager, Li approved on several occasions in 1995 huge
amounts of unpaid sales to a factory where his son was a special
assistant to the factory's director.
</P>
<P>
When the factory declared bankruptcy, several months later, it
still owed the company 49.83 million yuan, according to the
investigations.
</P>
<P>
The officials, from the Central Commission for Discipline
Inspection of the Communist Party of China and the Ministry of
Supervision, said that Li had seriously neglected his duties and
brought about huge economic losses to the company and the state.
</P>
<P>
All Party and government officials should learn a lesson from
Li's case, they noted.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Party and government departments at all levels
should enhance their supervision of leading officials, and those
neglecting their duties should be strictly disciplined, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
