<HEADLINE> MILF Stronghold in Mindanao Falls to Government Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Philippine government troopers
captured a stronghold of the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF)
in the southern Philippines on Sunday, a military update said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The military said in a report that 11 rebels were slain in the
military offensive and a government soldier was also killed in the
clash in Barira, Maguindanao.
</P>
<P>
Barira has reportedly been cleared of MILF rebels since 2:20 p.
m. Sunday before Military warplanes and attack helicopters pounded
the rebel stronghold.
</P>
<P>
MILF spokesman Eid Kabalu said the bomb raid resulted in the
destruction of MILF structures in the southern part of Barira,
near a valley located at the foot of Camp Abubakar.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the military confirmed that starting from Saturday
evening, the government troopers launched an air attack at the
Camp Abubakar, the MILF's center base located in Maguindanao
province.
</P>
<P>
This was the first wave of military offensive government
troopers staged since the two sides signed a ceasefire accord in
1997.
</P>
<P>
The clash between government soldiers and MILF rebels had
upgraded since January this year when the Philippine government
declared June 30 as the deadline for the peace talks with the MILF.
</P>
</TEXT>
