<HEADLINE> Philippine Military Capable of Curbing Terrorism: Estrada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- President Joseph Estrada said Monday
that the Armed Forces of the Philippines remains ready and capable
of thwarting terrorist and criminal acts committed by armed groups
in Mindanao.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 53rd anniversary of the Philippine Air Force
PAF), Estrada said ongoing operations prove that the government
remains committed to uphold the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
"We face today, while we confront the conflict in Mindanao, one
of the most difficult trials in fostering the unity and
preservation of our nation under one flag, one Constitution, one
government... And we shall overcome this...," he said.
</P>
<P>
The president said he is aware of the soldiers' sacrifices to
restore and uphold peace and the rule of law in the country.
</P>
<P>
He added the air support for government troops has shown the
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) that the government means
business in protecting the country's territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Estrada said, the June 30 deadline for a peace
agreement has already lapsed, leaving the government open to take
the needed action to preserve the country's territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
"The deadline already expired. So there will be continued
military operations," Estrada said.
</P>
<P>
In January this year, Estrada declared June 30 as the deadline
for the peace talks with the MILF, the biggest Muslim rebel group
in Mindanao, which has been fighting for a separate Islamic state
for more than two decades.
</P>
<P>
But the two sides failed to sign an interim peace accord before
the end of the deadline due to MILF's refusal to accept autonomy
proposed by the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
