<HEADLINE> Timely Rain Cools Beijing Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rain today gave Beijingers
relief from scorching temperatures.
</P>
<P>
A heavy downpour hit the capital at about 3:30 in the afternoon.
According to Beijing meteorological station, the rainfall will
also help ease a drought that has been afflicting North China.
</P>
<P>
The previous Saturday, Beijing's temperature reached 40 degrees
centigrade for the first time this summer.
</P>
<P>
The rain, caused by an eastward depression, will continue until
tomorrow afternoon, and the temperatures in the coming two days
are expected to be below 30 degrees centigrade.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Beijing has seen much less rain this
summer, as the rainfall in June was only some 20mm, much less than
the previous years' average of 70mm.
</P>
<P>
Local media reported that the continued hot weather has caused
electricity consumption to shoot up and drawn much more people
into air-conditioned shopping malls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
