<HEADLINE> Protection of Life Top Priority: Xinhua Commentary (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The commentary points out that the frequent occurrences of such
accidents demonstrate local governments and departments' ignorance
of industrial safety requirements and accident prevention. Some
local governments ignore the regulations and practice lax
supervision of industrial safety.
</P>
<P>
Though economic gains are one goal pursued by the socialist
market economy, a responsible manager should obey production
safety rules, says the commentary, adding that safety should
always be integrated with production and profits. Only industrial
safety can ensure normal economic operations.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says that the enterprise manager should be the
first person responsible for industrial safety, and a safety
responsibility system should be established in order to curb the
occurrences of severe accidents, and to protect people's lives and
property, as well as help nurture a favorable social environment
for promoting the country's reform and opening up and
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Industrial safety is closely related to the security of the
people's lives and property, political stability, and the progress
of the reform, says the commentary, urging local officials to take
a responsible attitude in order to strengthen their management
work on industrial safety, and take immediate measures to ensure
the safety of the lives and property of their workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
