<HEADLINE> Protection of Life Top Priority: Xinhua Commentary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Xinhua News Agency released
a commentary today urging local governments to give priority to
the safety of people's lives and property.
</P>
<P>
An explosion on June 30 killed 32 people and injured 17 people
at a fireworks factory in the city of Jiangmen in south China's
Guangdong Province, with 39 other still missing. The commentary
notes that the blind pursuit of profits by some departments caused
them to dare to ignore the central government's regulations on
industrial safety.
</P>
<P>
The article demands that severe punishment be given to the
people responsible for accidents that result in the loss of people
's lives and property according to law.
</P>
<P>
The cental authorities have always shown deep concern over the
issue of industrial safety. President Jiang Zemin has urged
governments at all levels to take measures to ensure industrial
safety, as well as to give top priority to the safety of people's
lives and property, the commentary continues.
</P>
<P>
The central authorities have stressed many times that local
governments and departments concerned should pay close attention
to industrial safety, which is very important for economic
development and political stability.
</P>
<P>
After an explosion in Pingxiang City in east China's Jiangxi
Province three months ago, which killed more than 30 people, Jiang
gave instructions to tighten up industrial safety, and so the
Jiangmen explosion came as a particular shock, it says.
</P>
</TEXT>
