<HEADLINE> Fourth China International Investment Fair to Open in Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Fourth China Fair for
International Investment and Trade (CFIIT) will take place in
Xiamen Special Economic Zone in September, organizers of the fair
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ma Xiuhong, assistant minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation of China, told a press briefing that the upcoming fair
will focus on attracting investment in priority industries with
western and central China as investment priorities.
</P>
<P>
"An International Investment Forum will be launched during the
fair for the first time, and an array of events for international
exchanges will be arranged," Ma said.
</P>
<P>
During the fair, Ma said, up to 10,000 selected projects will
be available to overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Since the first fair in 1997, the CFIIT has become a sole
national event for promoting direct investment from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The previous three fairs witnessed the signing of 6,708
investment agreements with a total contractual investment of 37.
249 billion U.S. dollars and a total value of 2.968 billion U.S.
dollars for import and export contracts.  
</P>
