<HEADLINE> 72 Arrested in Euro 2000 Victory Celebration on Champs-Elysees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Seventy-two people were arrested by
police for throwing bottles, smashing shop windows and cars and
attacking police during the celebration of the victory of the
French national soccer team in the Euro 2000 soccer tournament
Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, about 100 people were slightly injured in the
incidents which mainly took place on the Champs-Elysee in central
Paris, said police.
</P>
<P>
Clashes between about 400 troublemakers and police started at
around 1:00 Monday morning on the Champs-Elyees, where 400,000
people were celebrating France's victory.
</P>
<P>
Police used tear gas to disperse the youths who threw beer
bottles and tins at the law-enforcers. The battle lasted about one
hour and a half.
</P>
<P>
Among the some 20 shops attacked were the Disneyland shop and
some high quality sportswear shops.
</P>
<P>
One security guard of a shop was beaten up by several young men
and a cameraman of the France 3 television channel had his nose
broken when he was pushed by a crowd.
</P>
<P>
Medical rescuers gave emergency treatment to about 200 people
and sent 91 of them to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The celebration, reminiscent of that after France won the
soccer World Cup two years ago, broke out seconds after France
beat Italy 2-1 in extra time with a golden ball in the final match
of Euro 2000 held in Rotterdam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
