death by the High Court in Malaysia's northern state of Pulau
Pinang Monday for trafficking 189.86 grams of heroin, Bernama news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
David Anthony Chell, 57, charged under Section 39B (1) (a) of
the Dangerous Drugs Act 1952 which carries the mandatory death
sentence on conviction, was found guilty of committing the offense
at the Bayan Lepas International Airport in the state on October 7,
1998.
</P>
<P>
The court was satisfied with the evidence of the prosecution
witnesses who testified that the pouch which contained the drugs
was found in Chell's underwear, Justice Zaleha Zahari said.
