<HEADLINE> Five Terrorist Blasts Kill At Least 36, Injure 74 in Chechnya: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Preliminary reports indicate that 36
Russian servicemen were killed and another 74 injured in five
terrorist attacks in Chechnya on Sunday, Russian presidential aide
on Chechnya Sergei Yastrzhembsky announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
All the attacks "had one and the same signature, one and the
same scheme, with heavy 'Ural' trucks and suicide bomber drivers,"
