<HEADLINE> Slovak Prime Minister Assumes Presidential Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 3 (Xinhua) -- The Slovak government on Monday
entrusted Prime Minister Mikulas Dzurinda with executing
presidential powers at its special meeting based on a medical
report about ailing President Rudolf Schuster, the Czech News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Under Slovakia's constitution, in the event that the president
is unable to perform his duties, his power is transferred to the
government and parliament chairman.
</P>
<P>
Schuster, 66, underwent two "life-saving" emergency operations
after he was hospitalized on June 14 with a high fever. Later, due
to his deteriorating condition, Schuster was transferred to
Austria to receive an emergency treatment last Wednesday.
According to the latest information, his life is no longer in
danger, but the condition still remains serious.
</P>
<P>
Schuster was elected president last year. 
</P>
