<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's fund market was not
affected by the decline of the two stock markets and saw an active
trading Monday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 26 funds on Monday's securities investment fund market,
20 rose and 6 remained unchanged, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities company..
</P>
<P>
Investors paid close attention to Fund Taihe after it released
its interim dividend plan. It closed up 4.5 percent to be the
fourth gainer Monday. The other top gainers were Fund Zhujiang,
Fund Yuze, Fund Tongzhi and Fund Yuhua, which were all
restructured funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
