<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed down 0.19
percent, or 30.81 points, at 16,124.97 Monday amid sluggish
trading atmosphere ahead of U.S. July 4 holiday.
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of the benchmark Hang Seng Index (HSI),
only Properties rose on the government's decision to give up its
public housing plan.
</P>
<P>
The sub-index of Properties gained 1.79 percent while that of
Finance, Utilities and Industry &AMP; Commerce slid by 0.24 percent, 0.
01 percent and 0.68 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Market heavyweight China Mobile, formerly known as China
Telecom, shed 1.45 percent to close at 67.75 HK dollars
</P>
<P>
The turnover on Monday was 8.287 billion HK dollars (1.062
billion U.S. dollars), 1.5 percent up from the volume on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
China-related stocks ended slightly lower with the Hang Seng
China Enterprises Index down 0.53 percent and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index down 0.52 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index and the Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index
declined by 1.48 percent and 1.27 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The HSI opened 21.28 points, or 0.13 percent, higher at 16,177.
06 Monday before it dropped 77.01 points, or 0.48 percent, lower
to close the morning session at 16,078.77. 
</P>
