<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UAE Newspaper Hails Saudi-Kuwaiti Sea Border Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A leading United Arab Emirates
newspaper on Monday welcomed the signing of a maritime border
demarcation accord between Saudi Arabia and Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The Dubai-based Al Bayan said the agreement, signed on Sunday in
Kuwait, has boosted the hope that Arabs can solve their border
problems through negotiations.
</P>
<P>
"The accord has again proved that fraternal and cordial
solutions between Arab countries are the best way to solve
differences," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The accord is also another landmark in the cooperation among
members of the Gulf Cooperation Council, the paper added. The Gulf
Arab club groups Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the UAE, Oman, Bahrain and
Qatar.
</P>
<P>
"The agreement has also paved the way for holding amicable talks
between Kuwait, Saudi Arabia and Iran on the Dorra gas field, which
Tehran also wants to share," noted the paper.
</P>
<P>
The three Gulf states have been negotiating for years to work
out a demarcation scheme over the continental shelf where the gas
field lies.
</P>
<P>
A row erupted after Iran started drilling for gas in the
disputed area earlier this year, triggering concern and protests
from Kuwait and Saudi Arabia. Iran stopped the operations in May
and expressed readiness to open talks with Kuwait and Saudi Arabia
to reach an understanding on this territorial dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Emirates also hoped the accord could have exemplary impact
on a solution of its territorial dispute with Iran over three
islands near the strategic Strait of Hormuz, through which one
third of the world's crude oil passes.
</P>
<P>
The islands -- Greater and Lesser Tunbs and Abu Musa -- are
claimed by both the UAE and Iran, but now under control of Iran.
</P>
<P>
The UAE has called on Iran to settle the issue through either
negotiations or referral to the International Court of Justice in
the Hague. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
