<HEADLINE> China Demanding Vehicles to Use Clean Gasoline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China is demanding vehicles in its
major cities to use a new sort of clean gasoline in an effort to
curb heavy pollution.
</P>
<P>
According to an order issued recently by the government, the
new gasoline will be available this month in Beijing and Tianjin
in the north and Guangzhou in the south.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that China has invested more than ten billion
yuan (about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars) to upgrade the depurative
techniques and facilities.
</P>
<P>
The new gasoline can reduce car emissions by 50 percent, and
save oil by 3 to 5 percent, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The gasoline will be introduced nationwide in 2003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
