<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Down at Monday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market index
dipped 1.20 points, or 2.14 percent, to 54.82 at the close on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover stood at 10.02 million U.S. dollars (about 83.17
million yuan), compared with 8.81 million U.S. dollars last Friday,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities company.
</P>
<P>
The market opened flat today, but lingered in the red
throughout the session, as investors were worried about corporate
earnings ahead of interim reports due from this month.
</P>
<P>
For much of the day, trading was confined to a very narrow
range of one-and-a-half point, and no leading stocks provided
strong support for the market.
</P>
<P>
Declining shares outperformed advancing issues by 45 to 3, with
6 unchanged, Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Huili (900939.SS) rose 6.96 percent to 0.246 U.S.
dollars, while Dahua Chemical (900951.SS) grew 1.33 percent to 0.
152 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sh Refrig Comp (900910.SS) lost 5.45 percent to 0.208 U.S.
dollars, while Erfanji (900902.SS) fell 5.385 percent to 0.176 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Earning prospect continues to be the main focus of investors.
On elective buying interest, blue chips may lead any advance on
the market, which will continue to stick to a very tight trading
range. 
</P>
