<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Down Below 1990 Points At Monday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite index closed
at 1895.64 points on Monday, down 32.47 points or 1.68 percent
compared to the last close.
</P>
<P>
The total trading volume was 11.9 billion yuan (about 1.43
billion U.S. dollars), 5.4 percent less than the previous session'
s 12.58 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Affected by the rumor that the State-owned shares and legal
person shares may be listed, the Shanghai composite index dropped
sharply below 1900 points, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities company.
</P>
<P>
Two other factors also led the market to go downwards. One was
market expansion. Since last Friday, five companies issued new A-
shares on the Shanghai Stock Exchange, which have attracted a
large amount of money. The other was investors' concern over
interim reports of listed companies.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Friendship (Group) Co., Ltd. (600778.SS) was the top
gainer today with its price up 10 percent to the ceiling of 14.47
yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Three companies, including Hainan Hengtai Mango Industries Co.,
Ltd. (600097.SS), Ningbo Zhongbai Co. Ltd (600857.SS) and Shanghai
Dazhong Transport Co., Ltd. (600011.SS) dropped to their floors,
hit by selling pressure.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts with Homeway predict that the market is
likely to have a small rebound tomorrow. 
</P>
