<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-share Market Down 2.62 Percent at Monday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-share market index
dropped 2.99 points, or 2.60 percent, to 111.75 at the close on
Monday, approaching its intraday low at 111.53.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 53.04 million Hong Kong dollars (about 56.22
million yuan), in a sharp contrast to 159. 94 million Kong Kong
dollars last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The market opened flat today, but lingered in the red
throughout the session, as investors were worried about corporate
earnings ahead of interim reports due from this month, according
to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities
company.
</P>
<P>
Trading was restrained as investors were pretty cautious. And
as the session progressed, the rising stocks gradually edged out
the positive territory for lack of confidence.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmingly beat gainers by 52 to 0, with 2 unchanged,
Homeway analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Among the biggest percentage losers, Shenbao Ind (2019.SZ) shed
5.71 percent to 3.30 Hong Kong dollars, while Intl Container (2039.
SZ) fell 5.23 percent to 5.62 Hong Kong dollars.
</P>
<P>
As investors have been so dependent on earnings profile for
direction, this narrow range trading trend is likely to continue
at least until the next set of data, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
