<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Edges Below 600 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The total turnover was 12.1 billion yuan (about 1.46 billion U.
S. dollars), 12.3 percent less than yesterday morning's 13.8
billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities company.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen composite index dropped below 600 points today.
The drop is believed to be driven by the rumor that State-owned
shares and legal person shares may be listed on the market,
according to Homeway.
</P>
<P>
Two other reasons were market expansion, which caused a large
flow of money into the market, and investor's concern over interim
reports of listed companies, Homeway said.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin Beacon (0695.SZ) was the top gainer today with its
price up 9.24 percent to reach 18.08 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
China Great Wall Computer Shenzhen Co., Ltd.(0066.SZ) was the
biggest loser, with price dropping 7.8 percent to reach 21.99 yuan
per share.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to settle around 590 points tomorrow,
analysts predict.  
</P>
