<HEADLINE> Arab League Welcomes Kuwaiti-Saudi Sea Border Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League has expressed welcome
the signing of a maritime border agreement between Kuwait and Saudi
Arabia, Egypt's Al-Ahram daily reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters late Sunday, secretary general of the
Cairo-based Pan-Arab organization Esmat Abdel-Meguid lauded the
agreement as a historic move between the two Arab countries aimed
at resolving disputes peacefully.
</P>
<P>
"Such an agreement mirrors the deeply-rooted bilateral relations
binding Kuwait and Saudi Arab," the Arabic-language newspaper
quoted Abdel-Meguid as saying.
</P>
<P>
The chief of the 22-nation organization called on all the Arab
countries to solve any problems through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Saudi Arabia inked on Sunday the pact for the
demarcation of their sea borders. This step will also pave the way
for both sides to seek agreement with Iran on settlement of border
disputes in northern Gulf, found to be rich in oil and gas
reserves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
