<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 18th ASEAN Ministers of Energy Meeting Held in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The one-day 18th ASEAN Ministers of
Energy Meeting (AMEM) held here on Monday has called for
acceleration of the realization of an integrated trans-ASEAN
energy network.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN ministers of energy have agreed to accelerate the
realization and implementation of the ASEAN leaders' vision of an
integrated trans-ASEAN energy network consisting of the ASEAN
Power Grid and Trans-ASEAN Gas Pipeline Projects, according to a
join press statement released Monday afternoon at the end of the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN ministers held that its expeditious implementation
would significantly enhance economic integration in the ASEAN
region.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also acknowledged that the development of energy
infrastructure, diversification of energy supply, improvement in
energy efficiency and the utilization of new and renewable energy
technologies in ASEAN would greatly contribute to the region's
sustainability and security of energy supply.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN ministers underscored the importance of developing
master plans for the power grid and gas pipeline projects,
accelerating international and local finance and capital to bring
these energy projects to reality, promoting clean energy and
sustainable development, and creating a conducive policy
environment for energy trade and investment as priority
cooperation areas in the ASEAN energy sector.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Minister of Industry Dang Vu Chu chaired the meeting
with Pehin Dato Abdul Rahman Taib, minister of industry and
primary resources of Brunei, as vice-chairman.
</P>
<P>
The 19th AMEM will be held in Brunei in the first week of July
2001, said the joint press statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
