<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Improve Ties with Australia: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Alwi
Shihab said here Monday that the current political situation is
conducive enough for Indonesia and Australia to improve their
strained diplomatic Ties.
</P>
<P>
"The Indonesian government has been studying an exact time for
the President Abdurrahman Wahid's official visit to Australia,"
the minister said in a hearing with the House of Representatives (
DPR).
</P>
<P>
He said that Australia has showed an initiative to improve its
diplomatic relationship with Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
"Australia has also invited our president as well as other
parties in the country to visit Australia. And geographically,
Australia is our neighbor. It is important for us to live in
harmony. And this is a principle of our foreign policy," he added.
</P>
<P>
Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer paid a visit to
Indonesia on January 24-25 in a bid to clear the way to improve
bilateral relationship with Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it was reported that President Wahid will pay an
official visit to Australia some time next month despite protest
from some parliamentary members.
</P>
<P>
The relations between Indonesia and Australia have been
deteriorated since the U.N.-sponsored direct ballot held in East
Timor last August during which the territory voted in favor of
independence.
</P>
<P>
The military and trade relations between the two countries were
suspended after the ballot held in East Timor as the Indonesian
government suspected that Austria was fully involved in backing
East Timorese pro-independence camps. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
