<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Ranks 5th in Number of HIV People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenya now has the fifth largest
number of people living with HIV/AIDS in the world, the East
African weekly reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a 135-page report by the World Health
Organization and other U.N. agencies as saying that it is
estimated that 2.1 million Kenyans, adults and children included,
are now living with HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
South Africa has the largest number of people living with the
HIV virus in the world, followed by India, Ethiopia and Nigeria,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania has around 1.3 million people living with HIV/AIDS,
while the figure for Uganda is about 820,000, the report said,
adding that there are also about 1.7 million AIDS orphans in
Uganda, 1.1 million in Tanzania and 730,000 in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, nearly 15 percent of all young women between 15 and
24 are now said to be infected in Kenya, with the figure for
Uganda and Tanzania standing at about 9 percent, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Control Foreign Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government agencies and
parastatals have been banned from seeking new foreign loans to
effectively control the country's external debt standing at some
30 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Government has barred its agencies from taking all sorts of
loans from any external source," Nigerian press Monday quoted the
Special Adviser to the President, Philip Asiodu, as saying over
the weekend in Abuja.
</P>
<P>
The federal government will only take loans that are
concessionary or at rates as low as 0.75 percent, said Asiodu.
</P>
<P>
The government is currently negotiating a one-billion-dollar
stand-by facility with the World Bank to help fund its poverty
alleviation program, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
