<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodian Ruling Party Starts National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Cambodian People's Party (
CPP), the country's ruling party, started the 27th national
congress of its central committee on Monday, emphasizing on
national cooperation and unity.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, CPP Chairman Chea Sim said that his
party will cooperate and unite with its coalition partner -- the
FUNCINPEC Party, led by Prince Norodom Ranariddh, as well as other
patriotic forces to maintain social stability, develop national
economy, and improve people's living standard.
</P>
<P>
Chea said that his party never regards the kingdom's new
achievement as that of its own only, but as the result of the
participation of all patriotic forces, especially of FUNCINPEC.
</P>
<P>
The constantly changing situations both home and aboard offer
Cambodia plenty of opportunities for development, he said, under
which the CPP will concentrate efforts on carrying out its
scheduled programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
