<HEADLINE> Explosion in Chechnya Kills 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 3 (Xinhua) -- A track explosion in Gudermes,
Chechnya, on Sunday evening killed three Russian soldiers and at
least eight local residents, the Itar-Tass news agency reported
Monday, quoting the Chechen regional office of the Russian
Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The three servicemen, from a Russian reconnaissance battalion,
and the eight civilians were found dead after an explosive-laden
KamAZ lorry blew up near the battalion campus in the western
suburb of Gudermes, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Investigation is now being carried out by the Chechen
prosecutor's office.
</P>
<P>
Bombs believed to be planted by Chechen rebels also went off in
other cities of Chechnya on Sunday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Ambushes and assaults often occur in the region though Russia
has claimed an ending of the war in Chechnya. 
</P>
</TEXT>
