<HEADLINE> Highlights of Trade-Related News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights of
major trade-related news released by Xinhua over the past week (
June 26 - July 2):
</P>
<P>
 Foreign Economic Cooperation and Investment
</P>
<P>
-- The Industrial and Commercial Bank of China Monday signed an
agreement with Bank of America on the drawing of bank bills in
Renminbi.
</P>
<P>
This move marks the ICBC's advancement into a new business area
in international interbank cooperation, and it also makes the Bank
of America the first overseas bank to handle bank bills business
in RMB in China.
</P>
<P>
-- US-based BEA System Tuesday established cooperative relations
with the Beida Jade Bird Sci-Tec Co, a major software producer in
the country, to promote e-commerce development in China.
</P>
<P>
-- The Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) announced
Wednesday that it has established strategic cooperative
partnership with the United States' State Street Bank (SSB).
</P>
<P>
-- Italian insurer Assicurazioni Generali S.P.A. has got
approval from the China Insurance Regulatory Commission to launch
a life insurance joint venture in China.
</P>
<P>
-- Nokia has signed contracts recently with the China Unicom's
subsidiaries to provide Wireless Application Protocol (WAP)
solutions for them.
</P>
<P>
According to contracts, Nokia will provide Artus information
platform and application for Unicom's subsidiaries in Anhui, Hebei,
Zhejiang provinces and Chongqing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
-- World-renowned retail giants are investing more in China,
with the optimistic view of a better investment environment and
the hope of garnering a bigger slice of the huge pie.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Wal-mart, the world's No.1 retailer and the second in the
world's 500 giants, for instance announced this week that it will
continue to purchase goods from China in the coming years.
</P>
