<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egyptian Firm to Build Large-Scale Fruit Processing Plant in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 3 (Xinhua) -- An Egyptian import and export
company based in Kenya will spend 7 million U.S. dollars to build
a pineapple juice processing factory in Kenya's capital Nairobi,
the East African Standard newspaper reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Raouf Abokela, an engineer of Egypt East Africa, was quoted as
saying on Sunday that the company had acquired a one-acre plot in
the city and the ground breaking would start within a month's
time.
</P>
<P>
According to Abokela, the final paperwork between his firm and
the Kenyan government will be completed at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
Noting that such products as pineapple, tea, coffee and pawpaw
have a great potential in Egypt, the engineer disclosed that his
firm also plans to build a biscuit making factory in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Egypt East Africa is a distribution company representing 25
large Egyptian manufacturing companies with an annual combined
turnover of about 6 billion dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
