<HEADLINE> Uganda's HIV Infection Rate Down Dramatically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's HIV infection rate has
dropped from the highest inas the
highest HIV infection rate, with 25.84 percent of the adults aged
between 15 and 49 carrying the HIV virus, followed by Botswana
(25.10 percent), Namibia (19. 07), Swaziland (18.50), Malawi
(14.92), Mozambique (14.17) and South Africa (12.91).
</P>
<P>
Other African countries with higher adult HIV infection rates
than Uganda include Rwanda, Kenya, thnent, each with 0.03 percent, the UNDP report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
