<HEADLINE> Blast Rocks Apartment Block in Chechnya, Killing 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-six people were killed and 81
wounded in an explosion rocking an apartment building near the
Chechen town of Argun Sunday night, said the Russian Emergency
Ministry Monday.
</P>
<P>
However, the Itar-Tass news agency quoted a spokesman for the
prosecutor's office in Chechnya's city of Gudermes as saying that
at least 50 died in the incident.
</P>
<P>
The terrorist act had followed the old Chechen script: an
explosive-stuffed Kamaz truck was parked and blown up near an
Interior Ministry hostel. The employees of the Chelyabinsk
Interior Department were in the building at the time of the blast,
Itar-Tass cited the ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Interfax said a violent explosion of a truck loaded with
explosives outside a Russian Interior Ministry residence hall in
Argun, Chechnya, at around 5 a.m. on Monday killed 25 people and
injured 81 others. Four others were missing.
</P>
<P>
A team of rescuers airlifted to Chechnya from Nalchik has begun
the search for survivors, and an Emergency Situations Ministry Il-
76 transport airplane ferrying rescuers and special equipment has
left Moscow for Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Chechnya's law enforcement agencies said the militants staged
the explosion in revenge for their defeat near the village of
Serzhen-Yurt in the central part of the troubled republic.
</P>
</TEXT>
