<HEADLINE> Australia Drop Two Olympic Champions for Sydney Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SYDNEY, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Gillian Rolton and Wendy Schaeffer,
who helped Australia to win the equestiran equestrian team title
at the Atlanta Olympic Games, have been dropped for the Sydney
Olympics, according to the press reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Games champions Andrew Hoy and Phillip Dutton and
Barcelona double gold medallist Matt Ryan have been named in the
Australian equestrian team for the Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"It's a horse and rider combination which has to be considered
and Gillian and Wendy are still working with new, young horses,"
Australian equestrian team manager Gareth McKeen said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The horses being trained by Gillian and Wendy would not be
considered up to Olympic standard but I hope they continue on for
the 2002 world championships in Spain."
</P>
<P>
Hoy, who also won at Barcelona, will be striving for his third
gold medal while Dutton will be looking for his second.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 horse-rider combinations have been nominated for
the four member team and 12 riders and 13 horses will battle it
out for the four places on the dressage team.
</P>
<P>
Between August 27 and September 5, selectors will decide which
of the listed combinations will go into the Olympic venue for the
quarantine period.
</P>
<P>
The final decision on who will ride in the team and individual
competitions will be made the night before the competition.
</P>
</TEXT>
