<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Battling Severe Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China is going all out to fight
against a devastating drought that has ravaged northern China.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 million people are battling the severe drought
every day, said officials from the State Flood Control and Drought
Relief Headquarters here today.
</P>
<P>
Funds for drought relief have reached 830 million yuan (about
100 million U.S. dollars) since early this year, the officials
said.
</P>
<P>
Workers have used 6.12 million sets of machines and equipment
and dug more than 2.2 million wells to provide water for drought-
stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
The State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters is
mobilizing more people to provide water for schools, hospitals and
remote areas hit by droughts.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that a total of 14.4 million hectares of crops
had been affected by droughts in China; 13.7 million head of
livestock had not had access to enough water by June 13.
</P>
<P>
Northern China is hit by the worst drought since 1990 this year.
Shanxi, Shaanxi, Hebei, Inner Mongolia, Shaanxi and Gansu have
suffered from the prolonged drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
