<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Centenarians Exceed 10,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of centenaries in China
had exceeded 10,000 by the end of 1999, according to the latest
statistics released by the China National Committee on the Aging.
</P>
<P>
The statistics shows that the number of the country's
centenarians has nearly tripled that of 1949 when the People's
Republic of China was founded.
</P>
<P>
And the average Chinese life expectancy, which was merely 35 in
1949, now stands above 70.
</P>
<P>
An official with the committee attributed the increasing number
of Chinese centenarians to the improvement in living standard and
health care, as well as economic and scientific advancement.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese elder people are now leading an increasingly
colorful life, which has greatly contributed to the nation's
longevity. In 1999 alone, the elderly accounted for 20 percent of
all the Chinese traveling abroad.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government plays a key part in this regard, the
official said, adding that some local governments provide the
elderly with subsidy, free milk and regular medical check.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislature Deliberates Nine Draft Laws (1) EDS-Updates with Details </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature, the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC),
started its 6-day session here today to deliberate nine draft laws.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tabled with lawmakers today were the draft amendments to the
laws on product quality, customs, and patent rights, as well as
the draft law on farm seeds and the trust law draft.
</P>
<P>
Each of them had been reviewed in previous legislative sessions.
</P>
<P>
Draft amendments to product quality, draft law on farm seeds
and draft amendments to custom law are expected to be put to vote
at the end of this legislative session ending on July 8.
</P>
<P>
To better protect rights and interests of consumers and ensure
fair competition, an addition was made in the latest draft of the
product quality law amendments to prohibit government bodies in
charge of supervising product qualities from engaging in "
recommending" certain products or claiming to have "supervised the
manufacture" of certain products.
</P>
<P>
In the draft law on farm seeds, an addition was made that
imported seeds or seeds for exports should be quarantined when
crossing Chinese borders.
</P>
<P>
The latest drafts of the amendments to the custom law provides
encouragement to public tipping on smuggling crimes and forbids
local governments and department from interfering in its law
enforcement activities.
</P>
<P>
The long-awaited draft trust law submitted for first hearing
five years ago was tabled with lawmakers for a second hearing
today. But many said that it may need further investigations and
research even after tremendous changes over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Further revisions have been made to the amendments to the
patent law to regulate patent handling procedures in line with
international practices, as China is near certain to join the
world economic rule-making body, the World Trade Organization,
soon, lawmakers said today.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Legally Standardize Language Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislature prepares to
enact a law on language use nationwide.
</P>
<P>
A law draft on commonly used Chinese language was submitted
today to the 16th meeting of the Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee for deliberation.
</P>
<P>
In explaining the draft law to the meeting, Wang Jiaqiu, vice
chairwoman of the NPC Education, Science, Culture and Public
Health Committee, said that a uniform language has an important
bearing on the state's unification, national unity as well as its
social progress.
</P>
<P>
The languages of all nationalities in China should be equally
respected and freely used by the people, and any form of
discrimination against them must be prohibited, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
While popularizing the mandarin Chinese, the central
authorities encourage the people to learn all other languages,
Wang said.
</P>
<P>
The 56 nationalities in China have a total of 73 languages, 55
of which having written forms.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the draft law, the mandarin Chinese and the
standardized writing characters should be used throughout the
country. Meanwhile, minority languages can be used in the areas
heavily populated by ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Many linguists and languages experts said that various dialects
in localities have made it inconvenient for people to effectively
communicate and the random alternatives of writing characters
sometimes suggest wrong meaning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislature Deliberates Nine Draft Laws (2) EDS-Updates with Details </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four other draft laws, which were the law on the nationwide
written and spoken language, amendments to the law on the fishery
industry, amendments to the judges law and amendments to the
procurators law, were also submitted to the legislators for a
first hearing today.
</P>
<P>
The draft law on the nationwide written and spoken language
define the Chinese Han language as the only legal nationwide
language and promotes the use of it across the country.
</P>
<P>
But it also says that all languages, including the Chinese Han
language, are equal, and shall not be restricted in any way.
</P>
<P>
The law on fishery industry was amended this time to provide
more sufficient protection of oceanic fishing resources, such as
banning fishing activities when it is not the fishing season.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court and Supreme People's Procuratorate
proposed to revise the 1995 laws on judges and prosecutors today
to further raise the qualification requirements for the legal
profession.
</P>
<P>
A treaty on extradition between China and Uzbekistan, and a
consular treaty with Australia were also presented to the
legislators for deliberation and ratification, along with separate
criminal assistance treaties with Colombia and Tunisia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
