<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, July 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Oman's GDP witnessed a 10.4 percent in 1999
against 10.2 percent in 1998, said an annual report issued by the
Central Bank of Oman on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The rise in GDP was attributed to the increase in earnings from
the energy, crude and natural gas sectors, which accounted for 38.
7 percent of the GDP in 1999, while non-oil sectors, agriculture
and services, dropped by 2.2 percent, said the report. (Oman-GDP)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) will use a two-
board trading system, a main board and a development board,
starting on Monday, according to the Jakarta Post.
</P>
<P>
The JSX said that the main board would be used to trade large-
scale companies that have good track records, while the
development board was for those which had not met the conditions
required to be on the main board. (Indonesia-Stock Trading System)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB) said Monday that it
has increased the lending rates on its U.S. dollar loan facility
for the second half of the year from 6.46 percent to 6.53 percent
per annum.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement issued here, the ADB said the rate on
multi-currency loans for the same period, however, has decreased
from 5.72 percent to 5.68 percent per annum. (Philippines-ADB-
Loan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Some existing Gulf laws which hinder residents
from investing in the six Gulf Cooperation Council(GCC) countries
need to be revised, according to a latest study released by the
United Arab Emirates' Industry Bank.
</P>
<P>
Opportunities must be created to attract back part of the Gulf
investments abroad to help diversify investments and contribute to
GCC economic and social development, the study stressed. (GCC-
Investment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Altogether 18,156 cooperatives have been set up in
the whole of Myanmar since the country promulgated its Cooperative
Law in 1992 in line with the market-oriented economic system.
</P>
<P>
Among them, there are 8,236 agricultural cooperative societies
engaging in crop cultivation, 977 industrial producers'
cooperatives taking part in producing commodities and goods and 2,
018 credit cooperatives extending financial services, Minister of
Cooperatives U Aung San told a meeting here Saturday marking the
International Day of Cooperatives. (Myanmar-Cooperatives)
</P>
