<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Population Reaches Over 48 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's population is estimated to
have reached 48.12 million in 1999, an increase of 870,000 or 1.84
percent compared with 1998, according to a current report on
health for the year 2000 issued by the Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar population is projected to reach 50 million by 2000.
</P>
<P>
Of the estimated population, the male population accounts for
23.9 million or 49.67 percent, while the female population
represents 24.22 million or 50.33 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report said that 15.85 million or 32.94 percent are in the
age group of under 15 years, while 28.5 million or 59.23 percent
are in the working age group of 15 to 59 years and 3.77 million or
7.83 percent are in the age group of 60 years and above.
</P>
<P>
More than 75 percent of Myanmar's population reside in the
rural areas, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has a total land area of 677,000 square-kilometers(sq-
km) and its population density is at 70 persons per sq-km.
</P>
<P>
The country's population is estimated to reach 60 million by
the year 2010 and 68.5 million by 2020, the Myanmar Ministry of
Immigration and Population predicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
