<HEADLINE> 8 Killed in Clash between Philippine Government Troop &AMP; Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Seven rebels and a government
trooper were killed Sunday following heavy fighting between the
Philippine army and the rebel group of New People's Army (NPA) in
the country, a TV report said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the fighting took place Sunday noon at the
boundary of Trinidad and Danao in the southern province of Bohol.
</P>
<P>
One of the rebel casualties was reportedly an 18-year old
female fighter, the country's leading news channel ABS-CBN said.
</P>
<P>
Armed Forces Visayas Command spokesperson Michael Manquiquis
was quoted as saying that two Special Forces platoons were
deployed to Danao after receiving reports that the NPA has been
massing in the area.
</P>
<P>
Last Tuesday, about 40 NPA rebels attacked a Japanese
construction firm in Dimiao, Bohol.
</P>
<P>
The insurgents, armed with high-powered automatic weapons,
raided the motor pool of Kanematsu Philippines, Inc.
</P>
<P>
Manquiquis said the rebels attacked after officers of Kanematsu
reportedly refused to pay so-called "revolutionary taxes".
</P>
<P>
A week earlier, a police officer was also killed and several
others were wounded in a clash between police and alleged NPA
guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
