<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0260 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Agriculture Registers Heavy Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 2 (Xinhua) -- The loss in the agricultural sector
of the Czech Republic was much greater in 1999, rising to 2.1
billion koruna (57 million U.S. dollars) from 440 million koruna (
12 million dollars) in 1998, said the latest report of the
Agriculture Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the loss to declined farm product prices,
which went down by 11.7 percent in 1999 from the year before. The
price of the cultivated sector dropped by 15 percent and that of
the livestock sector plunged 10.5 percent, it said.
</P>
<P>
Of all farming organizations, agricultural producers'
cooperatives suffered the worst in economic returns, which
registered a surplus of 190 million koruna in 1998, but a deficit
of 768 million koruna (28 million dollars) in 1999, it added.
</P>
<P>
Economists have predicted that with the current unprecedented
drought in the country, the grain sector is set to suffer a big
decline and the loss in the entire agricultural field will be even
heavier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
