<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party Wins Parliamentary Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 3 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party (MPRP) has won a landslide victory in the
Mongolian State Great Khural (parliament) election held on Sunday,
according to an official of the party's press office.
</P>
<P>
He said vote counting showed that up to Monday morning the MPRP
has got 70 out of the 76 parliamentary seats.
</P>
<P>
The MPRP had been in power for 75 years until its defeat in the
1996 polls, which sent it into opposition for the first time in
the party's history.
</P>
<P>
With 96,000 members, the MPRP is Mongolia's largest political
party.
</P>
<P>
During the campaign, the MPRP, led by Nambaryn Enkhbayar,
promised to get the country out of crises and the people out of
poverty if it comes to power. The party also promised to form a
strong government for the realization of these goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
