<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greene Beaten in 100 meters at Britain vs US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- World champion Maurice Greene of the
United States suffered another defeat as he finished only fifth in
the 100 meters at the Britain vs US Challenge in Glasgow, Scotland
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Jason Gardner won the men's 100m with a time of 10.40
seconds. American Vince Henderson was second in 10.50 and Briton
Darren Campbell came third in 10.52.
</P>
<P>
Greene clocked 10.54 with a slow start and said the poor result
came from too much traveling.
</P>
<P>
Greene, world champion in 100 and 200 a year ago in Seville,
Spain, was fourth in the 100 on Wednesday in Athens, Greece, but
came back to win both the 100 and 200 on Friday in Rome.
</P>
<P>
The American team won the meet with 179.5 points to 170.5 for
Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
