<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Training Course to Fight Maltreatment of Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China has opened a training course on
preventing the maltreatment of children, and experts from Britain
have for the first time given lectures.
</P>
<P>
The course, held in this capital of northwestern province of
Shaanxi, was attended by 30 parents, who learned that beating and
cursing are not the proper way to love their children.
</P>
<P>
Ill-treatment of children has been widely reported across the
country, where the entry into a university is seen as the only
boat to carry the youngsters into a bright future.
</P>
<P>
In order to pass the fierce entrance examination, parents
usually force their children to study round the clock, and if the
children refuse to do so, they beat them. Some children have made
suicide for this reason.
</P>
<P>
Jiao Fuyong, with the Shaanxi People's Hospital, said that the
problem has aroused international concern and the training course
echoes the call by the United Nations. His hospital has opened a
hotline to receive children's complaints. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
