<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Machine Industry On Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's machine tool industry is
likely to end its loss-making dilemma this year, but obstacles to
achieve this goal still exist, an industry official said.
</P>
<P>
Since January, the industry has witnessed a double-digit growth
in terms of both output value and sales as compared with the same
period last year, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The Fifth China Machine Tool &AMP; Tools Commodities Fair and the
Fourth China International Machinery &AMP; Equipment Show which ended
Sunday in Beijing also indicate increasing demand for machine
tools.
</P>
<P>
But in the January-May period, the industry as a whole still
suffered a loss of 210 million yuan (25.3 million U.S. dollars),
the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It is likely that the machine tool industry will start making
profits by the end of this year as the industry recovers form its
five-year negative growth, said Yang Xuetong, deputy director of
the industry management department under the State Administration
of Machine-Building Industry.
</P>
<P>
The increasing investment in fixed assets sector, especially
the areas of water conservation, railways, highways and
telecommunications as well as technical upgrading in key State
firms, will create great demand for machine tools. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
