<DOCNO> XIE20000703.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing University Join Hands with Wuhan Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 3 (Xinhua) -- China's prestigious Beijing
University inked an agreement with two companies to jointly
develop optical and electronic products in Wuhan, capital of
central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The university and the two companies also reached consensus on
the set-up of a joint company, the Wuhan-Beiguang Digital Video
Industry Development Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the university will provide digital video
technology to the new company, while the other two will be
responsible for investment and management.
</P>
<P>
After completion, the project will yield an annual output value
of 30 billion yuan (about 3.6 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Wuhan has announced an ambitious plan to build China's largest
optical electronics information base.
</P>
<P>
Within five years, the city will try to raise the output value
of what will be known as "optics of China" to almost 120 billion
yuan (about 14 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
