<HEADLINE> Steels Claims Second Stage Win in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Tom Steels won the second
stage of the Tour de France on Sunday when he sprinted from the
fast finishers.
</P>
<P>
Steels edged Australian Stuart O'Grady as the pair hit the line
side by side. The photo-finish showed Steels' front wheel
centimeters ahead.
</P>
<P>
German Erik Zabel was third in the 194-km leg from the
Futuroscope theme park to Loudun while Britain's David Millar
retained his overall lead.
</P>
<P>
For most of the race Dutchman Erik Dekker, only 36 seconds
behind overnight, threatened that lead as he won three
intermediate sprints to earn time deductions which trimmed 16
seconds from his deficit on Millar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
