<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Voeller Appointed Germany Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Former Germany striker Rudi Voeller
was named national soccer team coach on a caretaker basis on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The German Football Federation (DFB) said Voeller would be in
charge until 2001. Bayer Leverkusen coach Christoph Daum, the
favorite for the job, will then take over after his contract with
his club runs out on June 30th, 2001.
</P>
<P>
Voeller, formerly the Leverkusen sporting director, replaces
Erich Ribbeck, who stepped down when Germany were eliminated from
Euro 2000 at the group stage after the team's worst ever
tournament performance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
