<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Snooker Star O'Sullivan Checks into Clinic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 2 (Xinhua) -- Snooker star Ronnie O'Sullivan has
checked himself into the Priory Clinic in a bid to kick a drugs
habit.
</P>
<P>
The news that the world number four has been at the
rehabilitation center in Roehampton for just over two weeks was
confirmed by the website TSNsnooker.com, one of O'Sullivan's
sponsors.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old's manager, Ian Doyle, was stunned by the news,
but vowed that his player would bounce back.
</P>
<P>
Doyle said: "It came as a shock to all of us that Ronnie had
checked into the Priory because those around him were unaware that
he had any kind of problem."
</P>
<P>
"This is not the kind of news you wish to hear about any player,
but at least Ronnie has been man enough to admit he has a serious
problem, and has done something about it for himself," he said.
</P>
