<HEADLINE> France Wishes to Reinforce Coordination of Euro Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 3 (Xinhua) -- France wishes to reinforce
coordination of economic and financial policies of the 11 euro
zone countries during its six-month presidency in the European
Union, said French Minister of Economy, Finance and Industry
Laurent Fabius Monday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the daily Le Monde, Fabius said that of
the priorities for the French EU presidency is to give more ``
visibility'' to euro zone countries on the international monetary
scene.
</P>
<P>
He said that the weakness of euro which has been seen since its
creation in January 1999 is partly caused by a lack of
coordination by its members.
</P>
<P>
A better coordination in the policies of exchange rate, budget,
tax and structural reform by euro countries is needed to
strengthen the single currency, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fabius is serving from now in six months as the president of
the council of economy and finance ministers of the 15 EU
countries and president of the informal council of the 11 euro
countries called Euro-11.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that from now Euro-11 be called ``Eurogroup'' as
Greece will soon join the euro zone.
</P>
<P>
He said that a strengthening of coordination by euro zone
governments does not mean a weakening of the independence of the
Frankfurt-based European Central Bank (ECB), which runs the single
currency.
</P>
<P>
``The ECB can only be happy with a clearer vision of the
policies carried out in the euro zone,'' he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
