<P>
Annan said the Government held "high hopes" that the
international support demonstrated at the May 15-16 Special Donors
Meeting in New York can now be translated into concrete action to
help meet the country's most critical needs, including the ongoing
National Program for Demobilization and Reintegration.
</P>
<P>
"I appeal to the donor community to make every effort to assure
an early fulfillment of the pledge made during the meeting so that
security and development projects can soon commence," the U.N.
chief said.
</P>
<P>
Annan stressed that the international community should remain
engaged in the Central African Republic and take the "extra steps"
needed to complete the task of consolidating peace and stability
there.
</P>
<P>
"In practical terms, this means strengthening the national
capacity of the country to provide for its own security in the
newly restored democratic order," Annan said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
