<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Congratulates Mexican President-Elect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso sent Monday a message to Mexico's president-
elect Vicente Fox Quesada, for his overwhelming victory Sunday
during this northern country's most competitive elections.
</P>
<P>
In the message, made known at Ministry of Foreign Relations,
Cardoso also congratulated the Mexican people "for the serenity
and maturity shown at this unique moment of their history".
</P>
<P>
Cardoso expressed his wish to work jointly with Fox to deepen
friendly relations joining Brazil and Mexico, as well as to
strengthen Latin American cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Mexico on Sunday experienced the most fierce elections in its
history, which gave as a result the election of candidate of
Alliance for Change, Fox Quesada and finished with the
Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI) which stayed in power for
71 years.  
</P>
